    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-04-06T10:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-04-06T10:00:00-05:00" n="602"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d602">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">852.6363/766: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Spain</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Hayes</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Madrid</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-04-06T16:00:00+01:00"
                            >April 6, 1943—4 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 9:27 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>822. British Embassy informed by London sympathetic consideration being given to
                    supplying aviation gasoline. Ambassador suggested to me consent for British
                    civil aircraft to land in Spain might be requested as compensation. While I am
                    not prepared to say that we should decline to furnish aviation gasoline until
                    concession for British airline to operate in Spain is obtained it would
                    obviously be desirable from our general point of view if a British or other
                    Allied airline were permitted to operate in Spain.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hayes</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
